# Next.js Frontend Rules

## Stack
- Next.js 14+ with App Router
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS for styling
- Zustand for client state
- React Query (TanStack Query) for server state
- Framer Motion for animations
- Lucide React for icons

## Project Structure
```
frontend/src/
├── app/                  # Next.js App Router pages
│   ├── (auth)/           # Auth-related routes
│   ├── (app)/            # Authenticated app routes
│   ├── layout.tsx        # Root layout
│   └── page.tsx          # Landing page
├── components/
│   ├── ui/               # Base UI components (Button, Card, Badge, Input)
│   ├── chat/             # Chat-specific components
│   ├── itinerary/        # Itinerary view components
│   └── layout/           # Layout components (Header, Nav, Footer)
├── lib/
│   ├── api.ts            # API client with auth
│   ├── auth.ts           # Auth utilities
│   └── utils.ts          # General utilities
├── stores/               # Zustand stores
├── hooks/                # Custom React hooks
└── types/                # TypeScript type definitions
```

## Conventions

### Components
- Functional components only (no class components)
- Props interfaces defined explicitly (not inline)
- Use `cn()` utility for conditional Tailwind classes (clsx + twMerge)
- Extract reusable components — don't let files exceed 200 lines
- Co-locate component, types, and tests

### TypeScript
- Strict mode — no `any` types except at API boundaries with explicit cast
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/intersections
- Export types from a central `types/` directory
- Use discriminated unions for state machines

### Styling (Tailwind)
- Mobile-first responsive design (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` breakpoints)
- Use design system tokens from the design system docs:
  - Colors: `blue-600` (Buddi Blue), `teal-600` (Ocean Teal), `amber-500` (Sunset Warm)
  - Spacing: 4px base scale
  - Border radius: `rounded-xl` for cards, `rounded-lg` for buttons
- Never use inline styles — Tailwind only
- Extract repeated patterns into component variants, not CSS classes

### Data Fetching
- React Query for all server state (API calls)
- Configure sensible staleTime and cacheTime per query type
- Optimistic updates for itinerary changes
- Error boundaries for graceful failure handling

### State Management
- Zustand for auth state, UI state, and trip context
- React Query for server-state (don't duplicate server data in Zustand)
- Keep stores small and focused (auth-store, ui-store, trip-store)

## Performance
- Use Next.js Image component for all images
- Lazy load routes with dynamic imports
- Minimize client-side JavaScript — use Server Components where possible
- Stream AI responses (WebSocket) — show tokens as they arrive

## Testing
- Vitest for unit tests
- React Testing Library for component tests
- Test behavior, not implementation (what the user sees, not what the code does)
